cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for unsupervised learning in computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new class of CNNs called deep convolutional generative adversarial networks (DCGANs), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of unsupervised learning and generative models also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the hierarchy of representations learned by the DCGANs, which could suggest it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses the learned features for novel tasks, which could suggest it belongs to cs.GR (Graphics).
